Fetches run details plus the ranking (when the run has finished)
and prints a single-screen summary: status, duration, per-agent composite
scores, top regressions. Intended for quick "tell me what happened" after
an eval.

For machine-readable output, use --json (which emits the full ranking
payload), or the underlying commands: `run get`, `run ranking`, `run scorecard`.

Exits 0 regardless of run verdict — this command reports, it doesn't gate.

Usage:
  agentclash run show <run-id> [flags]

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for show

Global Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts
